  "doc_id": "2865",
  "text": "Besides, even if this modeling problem is taken care of, one might be confronted to scalability issues. For instance, geostatistical filtering usually requires to build matrices as big as the number of observation points and to solve the associated linear systems [CITATION_1] . For seismic datasets, this size is that of the observation grid and therefore can easily amount to several millions of points. Hence, the filtering scheme should be scalable both memory-wise and computationally-wise if we are to apply them to such datasets.",
  "correct_citation": {
